{In the eighth chapter, we will cover the critical 8...h5 setup for Black.} 1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. d3 dxe4 4. dxe4 Qxd1+ 5. Kxd1 Nf6 6. Nfd2 h5 $5 {Black gains space on the Queenside and prepares a bind with ...h4-g5.} 7. h4 $5 {[%csl Rg5][%cal Gh4g5] stopping all of their Kingside expansion intentions. Of course, every move has certain drawbacks. In this case, we weaken the g4-square. Still, I believe the trade-off to be worth it for White.} Ng4 $5 {[%csl Rf2] The principled response.} (7... g6 8. f3 Bh6 9. a4 $14 {transposes to the previous chapter.}) (7... Be6 {can be met with the thematic} 8. f3 {[%cal Gf3e4]} Nfd7 9. Bc4 $14 {swapping the bishops. White remains on top.}) (7... e5 $6 8. f3 Be6 9. Bc4 $14) (7... a5 8. a4 $14 {doesn't change much. In fact, the b6-square has weakened, helping White's cause.}) 8. Ke1 {[%cal Gd2b3,Gf2f3] we want to play Nb3-f3 next. Immediate f3 runs into ...Ne3.} e5 (8... g6 {can be met with the thematic} 9. Nb3 Bg7 10. f3 {[%csl Rg4] kicking the knight away.} Ne5 11. a4 {following the plan of gaining space on the Queenside.} O-O 12. Bg5 Re8 (12... f6 13. Bd2 {[%csl Rg7][%cal Gd2c3,Gb1d2,Ge1f2]}) 13. N1d2 $14 {[%cal Gc2c3,Ye1d1,Yd1c2,Gg5e3,Ga4a5] with a clear edge for White.}) 9. g3 $5 {this rare seems to be quite testing. Instead of Nb3-f3, we prepare f3-Bd3.} b6 $5 {[%cal Gc8a6,Yf1d3]} (9... Be6 {can be now met with} 10. f3 Ne3 11. Bd3 Nd7 12. Ke2 $14 {[%csl Re3] The knight is super dangerously placed on e3.}) (9... Nd7 10. f3 Ne3 11. Bd3 $14 {[%csl Re3] Black will be extremely scared here.}) (9... Bc5 10. f3 Ne3 11. Bd3 {[%csl Re3]}) 10. Nc4 $5 {[%csl Re5][%cal Gf2f3] stopping ...Ba6 plans.} f6 11. f3 Nh6 12. Be3 {[%cal Ga2a4,Gb1d2,Gc2c3,Gb2b4] we now get the structure we hoped to get. White will now expand on the Queenside. A possible line is} Be6 13. a4 Nf7 14. Nbd2 Nd7 (14... g5 {doesn't change anything. All it does is it weakens h5.} 15. Be2 Nd7 16. Bf2 Bc5 17. Bxc5 Nxc5 18. b4 $14) 15. c3 Bc5 (15... O-O-O 16. b4) 16. b4 Bxe3 17. Nxe3 g6 18. Bc4 $5 {with a very easy position for White.} *

