1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Nge7 $5 {Another flexible attempt. Black is delaying ...Bd7 or ...Qb6.} (5... Nh6 $6 {While this motif remains popular in a lot of variations, this is usually weak.} 6. Bxh6 $1 gxh6 7. Bb5 $1 {an important idea in these positions. We want to reduce the pressure over the c6-knight.} Bd7 8. Bxc6 $1 {[%csl Rh6,Rh7]} bxc6 (8... Bxc6 9. O-O Rg8 10. Nbd2 $16 {[%csl Gc3,Gd4,Ge5,Re8,Gf3,Rh6,Rh7]}) 9. dxc5 Bxc5 10. O-O Qb6 11. b3 $16 {[%cal Gd1d2,Gc3c4,Gb1c3] White remains strategically better due to the safer king and superior pawn structure.}) (5... cxd4 6. cxd4 Bb4+ $6 7. Nc3 Nge7 8. Bd3 {[%cal Gd3h7] Black is struggling, as they cannot castle anymore.} Bd7 (8... O-O 9. Bxh7+ $18) 9. h4 $16) (5... f6 6. Bb5 $1 {thematic, and strong.} Qb6 ({another direction is} 6... Bd7 7. Bxc6 Bxc6 8. O-O Qd7 9. Re1 {[%csl Re6,Rf6][%cal Ge1e8] The pressure seems obvious.} Ne7 (9... O-O-O 10. dxc5 Bxc5 11. Nbd2 $16 {[%csl Re6][%cal Gd2b3,Gb3d4]}) 10. Nbd2 Ng6 (10... Nf5 11. Nb3 c4 12. g4 Nh6 13. exf6 $16) 11. h4 $14) 7. Bxc6+ Qxc6 8. O-O Bd7 9. Re1 Ne7 10. Nbd2 (10. dxc5 {1/2-1/2 (91) Cheparinov,I (2654) -Vallejo Pons,F (2712) Linares 2023}) 10... Ng6 11. h4 $14 {[%csl Rg6]}) (5... Qc7 {Black wants to play ...f6 next.} 6. Na3 $5 {[%cal Ga3b5] trying to exploit Black's move order.} a6 7. Bd3 f6 (7... Nge7 8. Nc2 $16) 8. Bf4 $1 Qb6 9. Rb1 cxd4 10. O-O $14 {Black's king is in the center while they have undeveloped pieces. This looks extremely scary for Black.}) (5... a6 {tried by Vallejo in a few games.} 6. Bd3 Bd7 (6... Qb6 7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. O-O $14 {[%csl Gc3,Ge5][%cal Ge6e5]}) 7. O-O cxd4 8. cxd4 Qb6 9. Be2 Nge7 10. Nc3 Nf5 11. Na4 Qa7 12. Be3 $1 {We aren't afraid of ...Nxe3.} Nxe3 13. fxe3 {[%csl Rf7][%cal Gf1f7]} Be7 14. Rc1 O-O 15. Bd3 $14 {White gets the desired structure and the bind they were looking for.}) 6. Na3 {[%cal Ga3c2,Rc5d4,Rc3d4,Re7f5,Yb2b4] preparing against Black's plan of ...cxd4-Nf5.} cxd4 ({starting with this dosn't change much.} 6... Nf5 7. Nc2 Be7 (7... cxd4 8. cxd4 {transposes.}) 8. Bd3 $5 {[%cal Gd3f5,Gd4c5]} c4 9. Be2 b5 10. Bd2 {since the Queenside is now shut down, White can expand on the Kingside without any fears.} a5 (10... O-O {can be met with} 11. h4 $5 {[%cal Gg2g4] with g4 coming up at some point later in the game. Note that} Nxh4 $6 {doesn't work due to} 12. Nxh4 Bxh4 13. Bxc4 dxc4 14. Qh5 $16) 11. a3 {[%cal Ga3b4]} Bd7 12. g4 Nh4 13. Nxh4 Bxh4 14. O-O O-O 15. f4 b4 16. axb4 axb4 17. Rxa8 Qxa8 18. cxb4 Be7 19. b5 Nd8 20. f5 $14 {[%csl Gd4,Ge5,Gf5][%cal Gf5f6] White keeps great attacking prospects.}) ({some players have tried this, but after} 6... Bd7 7. Nc2 Qa5 8. Bd2 {Black is struggling.} Qb6 9. dxc5 $1 Qc7 (9... Qxc5 10. Bd3 $16 {[%csl Gd2,Gd3]}) (9... Qxb2 $4 {runs into} 10. Rb1 Qxa2 11. Ra1 Qb2 12. Ra3 $18 {[%cal Gd2c1,Ra3a1,Rb2b1]}) 10. b4 Nxe5 11. Nfd4 g6 12. f4 Nc4 13. Bxc4 dxc4 14. Na3 $14 {[%cal Ga3c4] we'll win a pawn and keep a risk-free edge.}) (6... a6 7. Nc2 $14 {[%cal Gf1d3,Gh2h4]}) 7. cxd4 Nf5 (7... a6 8. Nc2 Nf5 9. Bd3 $16) 8. Nc2 {transposes.} Be7 (8... Qb6 9. Bd3 {[%cal Gc2d4,Gd3b5,Rb5e8]} Bd7 {threatening ...Nxd4.} (9... Bb4+ $6 {can be met with} 10. Kf1 {[%cal Ga2a3,Gb2b4]} Be7 11. h4 h5 12. g3 $16 {[%cal Gf1g2]}) (9... Be7 10. O-O Bd7 {transposes.}) 10. O-O a5 $5 {avoiding b4.} (10... Be7 {can be met with the thematic} 11. g4 {[%csl Rf5]} Nh6 (11... Nh4 12. Nxh4 Bxh4 13. g5 $18 {[%csl Rh4]}) 12. h3 Ng8 13. b4 $18) (10... Ncxd4 11. Nfxd4 Nxd4 12. Be3 Bc5 13. b4 $18 {wins material.}) 11. Kh1 Rc8 12. Rb1 h6 (12... Be7 13. g4) 13. g4 Nfe7 14. Kg2 h5 15. h3 $14) (8... Bd7 {doesn't change much. After} 9. Bd3 Qb6 {or} (9... Be7 {transposes.})) 9. Bd3 Bd7 {staying flexible.} ({can be met with} 9... O-O 10. g4 Nh4 (10... Nh6 11. Rg1 $18) 11. Nxh4 Bxh4 12. g5 $1 {[%csl Rh4]} Bxg5 13. Qh5 h6 14. Rg1 Bxc1 15. Rxc1 $18 {with a decisive attack for White.}) 10. O-O O-O 11. Bd2 $5 {[%cal Gb2b5]} f6 {Black had no choice but to open up the Kingside.} (11... Rc8 12. b4 $16) 12. exf6 Bxf6 13. Bc3 Be8 14. Qe2 Bf7 15. g4 {kicking the knight away from the active square.} Nd6 (15... Nh6 16. h3 $14) 16. Nb4 {[%csl Rc6][%cal Gb4c6]} Nxb4 17. Bxb4 $14 {[%csl Gd4,Re6,Gg4][%cal Gf3e5] Black is struggling a bit due to the weaknesses in the center and the lack of space.} *

